<TEXT>
a moderate earthquake struck the 
hollister area monday but no damage or injuries were reported 
the quake at 907 am measured 41 on the richter scale and 
was centered in an area 13 miles southsoutheast of hollister the 
us geological survey in menlo park said 
the richter scale is a measure of ground motion as recorded on 
seismographs every increase of one number means a tenfold increase 
in the strength of the shaking thus a reading of 75 reflects an 
earthquake 10 times stronger than one of 65 
on oct 17 a major quake measuring 71 on the richter scale 
struck northern california killing 67 people injuring about 3000 
and causing 7 billion in damage 
an earthquake of 35 on the richter scale can cause slight 
damage in the local area 4 moderate damage 5 considerable damage 
6 severe damage 
</TEXT>
