plea no matter how much i feel im innocent anthony laughing 
said outside the courtroom 
laughing a 42yearold mohawk pleaded guilty to single counts 
of possession of slot machines operating an illegal gambling 
business and resisting arrest under a plea bargain prosecutors 
dropped six other counts 
the plea came after a 90minute conference that followed 
assistant us attorney john brunettis opening argument in the 
trial 
laughing is to be sentenced feb 27 he faces up to 10 years in 
prison if given the maximum penalties for each of the three counts 
he entered conditional pleas to the gambling charges reserving 
the right to appeal the charges on the basis of indian sovereignty 
issues 
laughing and 12 other mohawks who were arrested in a july 20 
raid by state and federal law enforcement officers contend the st 
regis indian reservation is a sovereign nation and that state and 
federal laws do not apply there 
laughing said he wanted to get his case to the next federal 
level more quickly rather than endure an extended trial i am 
innocent and if i have to appeal this all the way to the supreme 
court i will he said 
