trial before us district judge neal mccurn because mccurn has 
ruled repeatedly in the governments favor 
mccurn earlier this year rejected the sovereignty argument in 
pretrial motions citing other indian cases where courts have ruled 
that federal and state governments have jurisdiction on indian 
reservations 
mccurn allowed laughing to remain free on 300000 bail but 
continued a us magistrates order that he report to authorities 
twice daily and be at home overnight to receive a call from them 
laughing owns tonys vegas international the largest of seven 
