agreed this year to meet every six months the last meeting was in 
may in cartagena colombia where president bush is scheduled to 
meet in february for a drug summit with barco and other latin 
leaders 
it is one of the oldest of a half dozen regional organizations 
that have tried unsuccessfully to achieve economic integration 
in recent years trade among the five andean nations has declined 
due to high tariffs 
