him whats a lad to do after the war he marries her and brings 
her to america coney island usa 
yadwiga exists to be the perfect wife slave she polishes his 
bedroom slippers practices judaism so she can convert never 
questions his many trips out of town to sell encyclopedias 
the trips are to the bronx home of his hot lover masha lena 
olin theirs is a passionate and totally physical arrangement 
despite the presence of mashas mother 
herman cant live without masha so he marries her he feels 
obligated to yadwiga and remains married to her as well 
but tamara anjelica huston is another story 
crippled by the nazi bullets she took in her hip at a death 
camp tamara is the woman who bore his children the woman who is 
allwoman and who knows him best her independence and humor about 
his current situation drive him up a wall still he does not want 
to lose her 
mazurskys touch is masterful he pulls just the right 
performances from his ensemble with little effort and retains the 
integrity of each character his camera is not judgmental if 
anything it acts as an understanding lover 
huston is marvelous shes strong witty vulnerable but 
independent sexy knowing charming and bitchy her accent is a 
little irritating at times but soon is obscured by an excellent 
piece of acting 
olin who so impressed with her role as one of the passionate 
lovers in the unbearable lightness of being gives a stunning 
and moving performance as the troubled masha 
stein is a polish stage and screen actress who makes her 
american movie debut with enemies she lends a tender grace to 
the simple adoring peasant woman and emerges a strong film 
presence 
silver does most of his acting with expressions and moves 
herman is a man who harbors many ghosts and who like many who 
survived the nazis is deeply scarred by history its what he 
doesnt say what he doesnt do that tells us who he is 
enemies a love story is a deeply felt testament to any 
survivor at any time and its universality is in its ability to 
caress the humanity and joy of everyday life 
the morgan creek production for 20th century fox is rated r 
</TEXT>
