<TEXT>
wedding bells are all right but those who get married in the 
oklahoma county courthouse in oklahoma city can no longer celebrate 
with rice or birdseed 
oklahoma county commissioners have voted to ban the throwing of 
rice birdseed confetti and other similar substances in and around 
the courthouse 
rice and birdseed traditionally have been tossed at weddings as 
symbols of fertility but the commissioners action apparently was 
not an effort to limit population growth 
commissioner fg buck buchanan says the policy was enacted 
