<TEXT>
heating oil futures soared monday on the new york mercantile 
exchange as forecasts for more brutally cold weather attracted new 
buyers to a market that has been climbing with barely a pause for 
five weeks 
on other other commodity markets monday precious metals were 
lower livestock futures were mixed and grains and soybeans were 
mostly lower 
heating oil futures settled 49 cent to 424 cents higher with 
the contract for delivery in january up 424 cents at 7466 cents a 
gallon a fouryear high 
unleaded gasoline futures finished 13 cents to 174 cents 
higher with january at 5451 cents a gallon crude oil futures 
settled 3 cents to 112 higher with january at 2222 a barrel 
the highest level since last april 
with subzero temperature readings boosting domestic demand for 
heating oil the entire energy complex has become a weather market 
the cold snap that descended on the nations midsection last week 
is expected to continue into this weekend bringing unseasonably 
frigid temperatures to most of the united states east of the 
rockies 
weve had weather markets in heating oil before but in my 
lifetime i dont remember a weather market developing this early in 
the season said james ritterbusch a energy market analyst with 
carson petroleum co a chicagoarea oil distributor 
weather markets can create huge profits for speculators but they 
are notoriously treacherous a hint of a change in the weather 
pattern can send prices plummeting 
the heating oil market began its climb from about 60 cents a 
gallon in early november amid concerns about tight supplies of 
heating oil in europe which also had an early runin with arctic 
weather 
but the european weather has since warmed and river levels there 
have risen with rain opening transportation channels that had been 
problematic 
a week or two ago you saw a lot of cargoes from south america 
being redirected from north america to europe ritterbusch said 
i think some of those ships are now going to be making a uturn 
precious metals futures fell moderately on new yorks commodity 
exchange as the dollar showed some strength prices opened sharply 
lower but trimmed their losses by midday with support stemming 
from tension over the shooting of a us soldier in panama 
gold futures settled 210 lower across the board with december 
at 41180 a troy ounce silver was 39 cents to 42 cents lower 
with december at 5565 a troy ounce 
