the country and the problems realestate debt might pose should 
prices of properties lag for an extended period 
some observers contend that the situation could become a primary 
contributing factor to a debtinduced business slump in 1990 
also analysts said traders began dumping stocks on fears that 
a yearend rally they had been anticipating might not materialize 
bank of new england shares led the active list down 1 at 7 on 
the heels of a 3point drop friday 
among other mortgage and regional banking issues citytrust 
bancorp fell 2 to 14 bank of boston to 16 shawmut national 
1 to 17 first interstate bancorp 4 to 43 federal national 
mortgage 2 to 31 and federal home loan mortgage 5 to 61 
the moneycenter bank group also came under selling pressure 
bankamerica dropped 2 to 23 chemical banking 2 to 29 
manufacturers hanover 1 to 31 and chase manhattan 1 to 31 
losers among the bluechip industrials included international 
business machines down 1 at 93 american telephone amp telegraph 
down at 46 usx down at 34 and mcdonalds down at 33 
marriott dropped 1 to 33 the company announced a restructuring 
program including a planned move out of the fastfood and family 
restaurant business but also estimated lower fourthquarter 
earnings 
volume on the floor of the big board came to 18479 million 
shares down from 24039 million in the previous session 
nationwide consolidated volume in nyselisted issues including 
trades in those stocks on regional exchanges and in the 
overthecounter market totaled 22324 million shares 
as measured by wilshire associates index of more than 5000 
actively traded stocks the market lost 5774 billion or 171 
percent in value 
the nyses composite index of all its listed common stocks 
dropped 328 to 19017 
standard amp poors industrial index fell 621 to 39360 and 
sampps 500stock composite index was down 637 at 34377 
the nasdaq composite index for the overthecounter market 
tumbled 781 to 43603 at the american stock exchange the market 
value index closed at 37086 down 464 
