<TEXT>
a federal bankruptcy judge on monday gave 
cashpoor braniff inc permission to sell valuable takeoff and 
landing slots in chicago and new york to american airlines 
braniff arranged an emergency hearing in federal bankruptcy 
court and obtained approval to sell one slot at new yorks 
laguardia airport and three slots at chicagos ohare international 
airport to american for 400000 
on dec 7 braniff won court permission to sell an airport gate 
in fort myers fla to american for 215 million us bankruptcy 
judge c timothy corcoran iii approved the sale on condition that 
750000 be set aside in case braniff is later liquidated 
corcoran indicated he would continue requiring some proceeds of 
asset sales to be held in escrow saying he was worried that 
nothing would remain for creditors if braniff were to be liquidated 
braniff creditors requested monday that the 400000 from the 
slot sale be placed in escrow with the revenue generated from the 
fort myers gate sale braniff attorneys agreed to the request 
since filing for chapter 11 bankruptcy protection sept 28 and 
drastically reducing staff and flights braniff has existed on 
emergency infusions of cash from the sale of assets 
the orlandobased carrier stopped operating all but a few 
charter flights and laid off most of its remaining employees nov 
7 its workforce is down to 275 employees from more than 4800 
before the bankruptcy filing 
lawyers involved in braniffs bankruptcy proceeding say that by 
selling its assets the carrier is trying to gain more operating 
time until it can devise a reorganization plan 
</TEXT>
