<TEXT>
wall street brokerage drexel burnham 
lambert group inc will pay a 225000 settlement to virginia in a 
securities and mail fraud case state officials said monday 
the junkbond dealer is also barred from soliciting new retail 
business in virginia for two years the state corporation 
commission said 
drexel has agreed not to solicit new business over the telephone 
or set up new retail offices in virginia for the 2year period 
after which the company can request the commissions approval to 
resume business in the state the commission said in a statement 
there are about 300 drexel agents registered in the state the 
commission said 
earlier this year drexel and its parent each pleaded guilty to 
six counts of securities and mail fraud in connection with a 
justice department investigation of insider trading 
the virginia securities act allows the commission to take action 
against a brokerage if it has been found to have engaged in any 
fraudulent transaction or convicted of any felony 
the settlement is based partly on an agreement between drexel 
and the federal government in which the company agreed to pay 650 
million in compensation and fines in the insider trading case 
</TEXT>
