<TEXT>
conagra inc said monday its net income rose 
128 percent for its second fiscal quarter giving the diversified 
food conglomerate record earnings for the period 
the omahabased company reported a profit of 639 million or 
52 cents per share for the quarter ended nov 26 compared with 
568 million or 47 cents per share in the same period last year 
conagra reported sales of 386 billion for the quarter up 36 
percent from sales of 284 billion in last years second fiscal 
quarter 
for the first half of its fiscal year net income was up 20 
percent to 1139 million or 92 cents a share from 95 million 
or 79 cents a share last year the company said net sales were 
787 billion up 39 percent from 565 billion last year 
charles m harper conagras chairman and chief executive 
attributed the results to conagras food chain balance 
as food industry conditions change different conagra 
businesses come to the fore he said fiscal 1990 is a case in 
point and we continue to expect record earnings for the full 
year 
he said there are many domestic and international opportunities 
for the company 
for example the current political trends in eastern europe 
hold considerable promise for a basic food company whose job is to 
help feed people better he said 
</TEXT>
