<TEXT>
ford motor co announced monday it is offering 
rebates of up to 1000 on all 1989 and 1990 aerostar minivans 
matching incentives announced last week by chrysler corp 
effective monday rebates on 1989 aerostars were increased from 
500 to 1000 and 1000 rebates were offered on all 1990 models 
ford said 
the incentives will be offered indefinitely the automaker said 
on friday chrysler for the first time began offering rebates on 
its popular minivans the dodge caravan plymouth voyager and 
chrysler town and country the rebates are 1000 chrysler 
dominates the market for minivans a class of vehicle it created 
general motors corp has not said whether it will offer similar 
incentives for its minivans 
the rebates come at a time of a continuing sales slump in the 
auto industry that has lead to widespread temporary plant shutdowns 
